{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3558457,"name":"","username":"robojack","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/49beb7/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-16T17:59:24.846Z","cooked":"<p>Our <span class="abbreviation">FIRST<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="For Inspiration and Recognition of Science and Technology"></template></span> robot for this year now drives “forward” to drop the coral and is working correctly.  We have added a roller unit to the “reverse” end of the robot to pick up and drop algae and that seems to be OK except you are driving in reverse.  Our driver has requested the ability to change the notion of forward to align with the task we want to do.</p>
<p>I can manually change the direction in the statement</p>
<p>m_drive.arcadeDrive( fwd , rot);</p>
<p>to m_drive.arcadeDrive( -1  * fwd  , rot);   and it works just fine.<br>
but would like to make the -1 a variable that can change with a button.</p>
<p>However I seem to be at a loss as to how to use a variable to represent the -1/+1</p>
<p>as in  m_drive.arcadeDrive( driveDir * fwd  , rot); where driveDir will be +1 or -1 and will be set by a button in RobotContainer.java</p>
<p>I’m still delving into java and find I understand a little more as time goes on but we just finished getting the algae mover unit finished on Friday and while it’s working OK as is I’d like to see if we can make this change.</p>
<p>What we would like to do is use a pair of buttons on the joystick (.onTrue or .toggleOnTrue) to change the direction to fit the mode we’re in.</p>
<p>I’ll be looking into how to do it but could use some help if someone has a suggestion.  (Competition starts next Friday)</p>
<p>Any help appreciated and sorry if this has an obvious answer.</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2025-03-16T17:59:24.846Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":94,"readers_count":93,"score":28.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":495795,"topic_slug":"dynamically-changing-the-fwd-value-in-arcadedrive","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":60576,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/dynamically-changing-the-fwd-value-in-arcadedrive/495795/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3558471,"name":"Emre ","username":"DukeEmree","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/dukeemree/{size}/251833_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-16T18:18:59.709Z","cooked":"<p>Something like this should work:</p>
